    <font face="Arial,Helvetica,Geneva,Swiss,SunSans-Regular" size="3"><b>Take Advantage of Accurint&reg; Case Connect within your Agency</b></font>
    <font face="Arial,Helvetica,Geneva,Swiss,SunSans-Regular" size="2"><br><br>
    Activate LexisNexis&reg; Accurint&reg; Case Connect within your agency today to take advantage of the two key components behind its power:&nbsp; 1) The Case Deconfliction Tool and 2) The Case Audit Compliance tool.
    <ul>
      <li>Accurint&reg; Case Audit Compliance enhances your Auditor's ability to view and track user activity within and across your agency for improved security and internal investigations.
      <li>Accurint&reg; Case Deconfliction provides your agency with Real-Time Information Exchange and enables the Information Sharing for Safer More Effective Investigations.&nbsp; It also can add value to your current public records searches by linking directly to existing searches such as Person Search, Advanced Person Search, Driver's License Search, Motor Vehicle Search, Criminal Searches and others to further improve your workflow.
    </ul>
    Accurint Case Connect is an integrated add-on tool that leverages an innovative data technology and power of public records data to enable law enforcement agencies to easily manage, share and compare case investigations case notes and information, both internally and with external agencies.
    <ul>
      <li><b>Case Audit, a tool powered by Accurint Case Connect,</b> This audit compliance tool allows management to search and review internal agency log files.&nbsp; This will allow for the detection of internal misuse of public record searches for non-work related purposes.&nbsp; Searches audited allowed based on input criteria, such as SSN, Name, Business Name and/or Address or by user name, to see all searches performed by a particular user.
      <li><b>Case Deconfliction, a tool powered by Accurint Case Connect,</b> will auto-notify two or more Users that have searched on the same record, either inter-agency or intra-agency, including other external Law Enforcement and/or Government Users (as allowed by your Administrator) to agree to connect to discuss case similarities.&nbsp; This tool can improve case investigations and workflow efficiencies by the cross-referencing of two agents' searches so that they may decide to share case notes and improve officer safety by collaborating on their investigations.&nbsp; This tool now also can further enhance your existing search tools by adding visibility into other searches like Driver's License Search, Motor Vehicle Search, Criminal Searches and others.&nbsp; In addition to the existing deconfliction matching by SSN, LexID<sup>SM</sup> and Phone the tool will also make connections by other key search identifiers such as DL#, VIN#, Tag/Plate, APN# and DOC#, along with an improved Case Deconfliction Management for viewing and managing alerts.
    </ul>
    Please note that this functionality is included in all price plans and can be enabled at no cost to your agency.&nbsp; To enable this functionality for your Accurint account, please contact your Account Representative today.&nbsp; Once Case Audit is enabled for your Accurint account, please click the My Account link in the View menu to access Case Audit.
